text: Frisco Peak is a summit near the north‑center edge of Beaver County, Utah, United States. ==Description== The peak, elevation , is located within the San Francisco Mountains range and is the highest peak within the range. It looks over the Wah Wah Valley to the west. Because of its relative location and elevation, it is the site of multiple radio transmission facilities. The name of the peak is a contraction of the mountain range in which it is located. ==See also== * List of mountains in Utah ==References== Category:Mountains of Utah Category:Mountains of Beaver County, Utah
title: Frisco Peak (Utah)
